---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";

const title = "GCP load balancing pricing: model hours, requests, and traffic processed";
const description =
  "A driver-based approach to load balancer cost: hours, request volume, and GB processed/egress. Includes a workflow to estimate GB from RPS and response size.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What usually drives load balancer cost?",
    a: "Time and traffic processed are common drivers. For internet-facing apps, outbound egress is often the largest variable.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do I estimate quickly?",
    a: "Estimate monthly requests and average response size to get monthly GB, then split load balancer vs egress as separate lines.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do I validate?",
    a: "Validate peak traffic and retry storms, and validate whether traffic is served via CDN (changing origin egress).",
  },
];
---
<GuideLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/guides/gcp-load-balancing-pricing"
  lastUpdated="2026-01-22"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p>
    Load balancer estimates get accurate when you treat them as: hours + requests + traffic processed. Egress is usually a
    separate, often larger line item for public services.
  </p>

  <h2>1) Hours</h2>
  <p>Count load balancers and hours per month per environment.</p>

  <h2>2) Requests</h2>
  <p>Convert RPS to monthly requests and split high-volume endpoints if needed.</p>
  <p>
    Tool: <a href="/calculators/rps-to-monthly-requests-calculator/">RPS â†’ requests</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>3) Traffic processed and egress</h2>
  <p>
    Use average response size to estimate GB transferred. Split origin egress vs CDN edge bandwidth and validate cache hit
    rate behavior if you use a CDN.
  </p>
  <p>
    Tools: <a href="/calculators/api-response-size-transfer-calculator/">Response transfer</a>,{" "}
    <a href="/calculators/data-egress-cost-calculator/">Egress</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Validation checklist</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Validate peak traffic and burst behavior (capacity and scaling depend on peaks).</li>
    <li>Validate retries/timeouts that multiply request volume and transfer volume.</li>
    <li>Validate CDN usage and avoid double-counting origin egress and edge bandwidth.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Related tools</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a class="btn" href="/calculators/rps-to-monthly-requests-calculator/">Requests</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/calculators/api-response-size-transfer-calculator/">Transfer</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/calculators/data-egress-cost-calculator/">Egress</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/guides/network-transfer-costs/">Network transfer costs</a>
  </div>
</GuideLayout>

